content.en-US:
## Development and coding services

Technological environment is constantly changing. At Helau, we have years of experience in being at the forefront of digital development. We don't shy away from old technology, but our goal is always to implement projects using the latest possible technologies.

## Our vision

We want to build sustainable, functional, and user-friendly digital services for our customers, with maintenance and security solutions that are based on best practices.

## Our mission

We are on a journey towards a more cohesive, inclusive digital era, where an increasingly large group of people have the opportunity to benefit from life-enhancing digital services. We want to ensure that in the future, as many people as possible are involved in the development of digital services.

## Our strategy

We implement our mission through our customer work, by providing our customers with visibility into different ways to develop their own digital portfolios. Digital service development has become an increasingly central part of our clients' core functions. By developing fair digital services, we improve the overall impact of businesses.

description.en-US: Toteutamme digikehitysprojektit palvelumuotoilulähtöisesti - suunnittelusta  koodaukseen asti.

content.en-US:
Digiprojektissa on otettava huomioon sekä saavutettavuus että selkeiksi jäsennellyt käyttäjien tarpeet.

Helppokäyttöisyys on monimutkaisten ja yksilöllisten kokemusten summa. On tärkeää miettiä digitaalista palvelua monen eri käyttäjän näkökulmasta.

### Digitalinen- ja kokemussuunnittelu

Kestävälllä tavalla toteutettu teknologia tarvitsee aina tuekseen kestävää sunnittelua. 

Ennen kuin hyppäämme asioiden edelle on digihankkeessa aina suunnitteltava kenelle, miksi ja miten toteutamme projektin.

### Strateginen suunnittelu

On paljon tilanteita jossa asiakkaamme ovat valmiita ottamaan teknologisen harppauksen mutta eivät ole aivan varmoja kuinka aloittaa.

On ensisijaisen tärkeää piirtää selkeä tiekartta siitä, millä tavoilla toteutamme suunnitellun vision.

### Konseptikehitys

Kun olemme testanneet uutta ideaa liiketoiminnan kautta, luomme konseptin siitä millainen ensimmäinen versio uudesta hankkeesta syntyy. Tätä “Minimum Viable Product” -tuotetta testaamme ja viilaamme lopulliseksi tuotteeksi.

- Modernit Headless CMS -palvelut 
Räätälöidyt front-end ratkaisut, kuten WordPress, Drupal ja muut perinteiset verkkosivualustat ovat saaneet seurakseen uuden Contentful CMS järjestelmän, jonka avulla voimme kustomoida loputomasti verkkopalveluitanne kaikkien vaatimusten mukaisiksi. 

Nämä palvelut sopivat erityisen hyvin, mikä tarvitsette erityisiä toiminnallisuuksia verkkopalvelullenne joita on hankala toteuttaa perinteisemmillä tavoilla.

- React.js kehitys 
Modernit react.js ja react-native kehitysprojektit. Kehitysympäristöjen pystyttämisestä lähtien kokonaisvaltainen hankekehitys.

- Kustomoidut verkkokaupat WooCom ja Shopify
Suuret ja pienet verkkokauppahankkeet toteutamme käyttäen viimeisimpiä teknologioita joita tarjoavat WooCommerce ja Shopify. Toteutamme kustomoidusti yrityksesi tai organisaatiosi tarpeiden mukaisen, käytettävyys ja visuaalinen ilme edellä toteutetun verkkokauppaympäristön

- Arkkitehtuuri ja Dev Ops palvelut
Kaikkien hankkeiden taustalla tarjoamme AWS palveluiden pystyttämisen sekä ylläpidon tarpeittesi mukaan. On tärkeää suunnitella selkeä kuva siitä millä tavalla hanketta lähestytäään, jotta saavutetaan pitkän aikavälin tavoitteet ja tulos on ylläpidessävissä vielä vuosienkin päästä.

title.en-US: MyDigiMap SaaS service for Tahto Group Oy

leadingText.en-US: The MyDigiMap SaaS product is designed to help companies plan, design, and manage their IT architecture with ease.

description.en-US: Over the course of a year, Helau Creative took on a project for Tahto Group, a company that provides IT solutions and consulting services to businesses. The project was to create a new SaaS product named MyDigiMap that would help companies manage their IT architecture and lead their IT transformations.

In this article, we will explore how Helau Creative created Hyperfigures, a centralized SaaS service that allows companies to control all their data in one place. We will delve into the technology stack used, the benefits of using the platform, and how it solves the problem of traditional data management.

content.en-US:
Building a World Class Corporate Architecture SaaS for a Finnish IT-consultancy.

- Brand Design
- SaaS UX and Product Design
- Front-end Development
- Marketing Material and Web Design & Development (WordPress)

The Product Design Phase of the project started with creating mockups and rough wire frame designs of the service. These designs were used for elaborating concepts and developing quick prototypes for testing. The complexity of the product and the domain set their own challenges for the process but with team work and excellent management we managed to build sophisticated designs for the service.

__Project Manager__:
Tuukka Miettinen

__Backend Development__:
Joona Hämäläinen

__Product Owner__:
Lasse Miettinen

__Lead Developer & Product Designer__:
Aleksanteri Heliövaara
[www.mydigimap.com](https://mydigimap.com)

Managing data can be a daunting task for many companies. With the abundance of data available, it can be challenging to keep track of it all. Companies often use multiple tools to manage their data, which can lead to a fragmented system. This can make it difficult to obtain accurate insights and make informed decisions.

Hyperfigures was created to solve this problem. It provides a centralized platform for companies to store and manage all their data in one place. This makes it easy to access and analyze data from different sources, providing accurate insights to make informed business decisions.

Hyperfigures was built using the latest technology stack. The frontend of the platform was created using React, a popular JavaScript library for building user interfaces. React is known for its fast rendering speed and reusable components, making it an ideal choice for building a responsive web application.

The backend of the platform was built using Node, a popular JavaScript runtime environment. Node provides a scalable and efficient platform for building server-side applications. It also provides access to a vast library of modules that can be used to enhance the functionality of the platform.

To manage user authentication, Hyperfigures uses Auth0, a cloud-based identity and access management platform. This allows users to securely log in to the platform and access their data.

To control data streams, Hyperfigures uses GraphiQL, a powerful tool for exploring, querying, and documenting GraphQL APIs. This provides a simple and efficient way to manage data streams, making it easy to access and analyze data from different sources.
[www.hyperfigures.com](https://www.hyperfigures.com/)

title.en-US: Solutions Architecture and Azure Migration for a SaaS

leadingText.en-US: Migrating a SaaS service from a POC solution architecture to a scalable Azure environment

description.en-US: Service and Solution Architecture for a SaaS

content.en-US: How to plan, build and migrate a scalable Azure environment for a full-stack SaaS service?

MyDigiMap SaaS had been built on a PHP Laravel framework and deployed with development and staging environments to Laravel Forge service and Digital Ocean Ubuntu virtual machine for production using Docker. 

Preliminary technology stack:

- PHP & MySQL Backend
- React.js Front-end with Context API stage management
- Laravel Framework 
- Docker container
- Auth0 IAM solution
- Digital Ocean Deployment

The app included an built in JavaScript front-end, using React.js that had been embedded to the Laravel build and a MySQL database that was built on local development environments for local development. This architecture was problematic considering scalability of the app.

- API connections to third party services difficult to execute
- Business Logic layer difficult to identify
- Development requires all code in one repository and code splitting difficult
- Locally developed builds required database on local machine
- Front-end development slow due Laravel build times
- Deployment and hosting expenses difficult to manage
- Multiple clients API connections not possible without complex authentication challenges

The client organisation was working in Microsoft environment so the Azure Cloud services were a natural choice for the migration. 

The steps to transform the solution and team for the migration required following planning steps:

- Environments and their respectful repositories and pipelines in Azure Dev Ops
- Resource groups and app services in Azure portal
- Separation of backend and frontend services in the current app solution
- Clear respectful responsibilities in the development team
- Authentication flow and required authentication steps 
- API Gateway design 
- Redefining business logic layer

The benefits for the microservice architecture and separation of backend and front-end layers opened possibilites for API connectivity to customer data without specific client connection with respectful authentication only. Thus the front-end needed a new, in this case Node.js express server for it's own business logic, that in the future will open possibilities for more complex front end behaviour, like real time messaging and native app -like behaviour. 

Separating front-end and backend repositories transformed the code base into individually manageable instances and improved continuous integration.

Benefits of migration to Azure also included CI pipeline improvements and managing deployment environments separately for the backend and front end. Azure contains variety of tools such as API managers ect. that can later be implemented to improve data flow and management.
